                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-571" type="given" value="WALTER"></interp>WALTER LUCAS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a coach painter, and lodge in Bouverie-street, where the prisoner lodged—I lodged there first—I believe the prisoner is an errand-boy—he slept in the same room with me—on the evening of the 27th of August I missed my property from where I lodge—I was at work in the afternoon, and when I came back it was gone—he slept there that night—I never gave him leave to pawn my clothes—these are the clothe—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them</hi>)—there is a pair of trowsers and a jacket—they were in box—it was not locked.</p>
